Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Microbiome diversity and optimization strategies
Elimination diet design and supervised reintroduction
Probiotic strain selection for specific conditions
Prebiotic fiber sources and progressive loading
Fermented food integration (kimchi, kefir, sauerkraut, kombucha)
IBS symptom management (non-clinical guidance)
Low FODMAP diet implementation and reintroduction
Gut-brain axis awareness and stress-digestion link
Food sensitivity identification through systematic tracking
Digestive enzyme and HCl considerations

Methodologies & Frameworks
Diet Protocols: Low FODMAP (Monash University), Elimination diet (IFM model), Anti-inflammatory diet, Specific Carbohydrate Diet
Probiotic Science: Strain-specific recommendations (Lactobacillus, Bifidobacterium, Saccharomyces), CFU dosing, timing
Fiber Framework: Soluble vs. insoluble, progressive loading (5g/week increases), diverse fiber sources
Assessment: Bristol Stool Scale, symptom severity scoring, food-symptom diary correlation
Fermented Foods: Traditional preparation, live culture verification, gradual introduction
Gut-Brain: Vagal tone connection, stress impact on motility, HPA axis influence

Reference Documentation
1. Microbiome Optimization
Comprehensive guide covering:
- Diversity as the key metric of gut health
- 30+ different plant foods per week target
